Tollhouse Cookies
Ingredients
	•	½ cup (110g) caster sugar
	•	¼ cup (55g) brown sugar
	•	125g butter, softened
	•	1 egg
	•	1 tsp vanilla extract
	•	1¼ cups (185g) plain flour
	•	pinch of salt
	•	½ tsp bicarb
	•	100g choc chips

Method 
	1.	Preheat oven to 180 degrees celsius
	2.	Grease or line baking trays
	3.	Sift flour, bicarb and salt together
	4.	Using an electric mixer, cream butter with the sugars until light and fluffy
	5.	Add egg and vanilla and beat well
	6.	Stir in sifted dry ingredients
	7.	Add choc chips
	8.	Drop teaspoons of mixture onto baking trays 5cm apart
	9.	Bake for 10 minutes
	10.	Transfer to wire racks to cool